cs.SC, cs.NA, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.CG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with iterative methods on the coefficients of the rational univariate representation (RUR) of a given algebraic set, which is a topic related to symbolic computation. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses the certification of approximate roots of polynomial systems via the recovery of an exact RUR from approximate numerical data. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper mentions the analysis of parallel complexity of different versions of the global Newton iteration. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the comparison of two natural approaches to define locally quadratically convergent iterations. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the computation of the RUR of an algebraic set, which is a topic related to computational geometry.
